1. Creating and Renaming Files/Directories
Commands: mkdir test_dir cd test_dir touch example.txt mv example.txt renamed_example.txt  Explanation: Creates directory, file and renames it.
2. Viewing File Contents
Commands: cat /etc/passwd head -n 5 /etc/passwd tail -n 5 /etc/passwd  Explanation: Displays full, first 5 lines and last 5 lines.
3. Searching for Patterns
Command: grep "root" /etc/passwd  Explanation: Searches for lines containing 'root'.
4. Zipping and Unzipping
Commands: zip -r test_dir.zip test_dir unzip test_dir.zip -d unzipped_dir  Explanation: Compress and extract directory.
5. Downloading Files
Command: wget https://example.com/sample.txt  Explanation: Downloads file from internet.
6. Changing Permissions
Commands: touch secure.txt chmod 444 secure.txt  Explanation: Makes file read-only for everyone.
7. Environment Variables
Command: export MY_VAR="Hello, Linux!" echo $MY_VAR  Explanation: Creates and displays environment variable.
